Read HTP data

read_HTP.Rd

Read HTP data

Usage

read_HTP(data, genotype, time, plot, traits, row, range)

Arguments

data

A data.frame in a wide format.

genotype

A character string indicating the column in data that contains genotypes.

time

A character string indicating the column in data that contains the time points.

plot

A character string indicating the column in data that contains the plot IDs.

traits

A character vector specifying the traits for which the models should be fitted.

row

A character string indicating the column in data that contains the row coordinates.

range

A character string indicating the column in data that contains the range coordinates.

Value

An object of class read_HTP, with a list of:

summ_traits

A data.frame containing a summary of the traits.

exp_design_resum

A data.frame containing a summary of the experimental design.

locals_min_max

A data.frame containing local maximums and minimuns

dt_long

A data.frame in long format.

Examples

library(exploreHTP)
data(dt_potato)
dt_potato <- dt_potato
results <- read_HTP(
  data = dt_potato,
  genotype = "Gen",
  time = "DAP",
  plot = "Plot",
  traits = c("Canopy", "PH"),
  row = "Row",
  range = "Range"
)
print(results)
